column2: ezANOVA(score, dv= net.score, wid= worker_id, within=humanPaddleSize)
Collapsing data to cell means. *IF* the requested effects are a subset of the full design, you must use the "within_full" argument, else results may be inaccurate.
There is at least one numeric within variable, therefore aov() will be used for computation and no assumption checks will be obtained.
